  "texts": [
    "By Definition 5.52.2, to show X ′ ∈ P ′, it suffices to show that there is anX ∈ P = RO(S, ⊑) such that X ′ = X ∩ S ′.",
    "Where ⇓X ′ = {x ∈ S | ∃y ∈ X ′: x ⊑ y}, let X = int(cl(⇓X ′)), so X ′ ⊆ X ∈ RO(S, ⊑) by Fact 2.17.2.",
    "It remains to show that X ∩ S ′ ⊆ X ′.",
    "Suppose x ∈ S ′.",
    "Then if x ̸ ∈ X ′,refinability for X ′ with respect to ⊑ ′ gives us a y ⊑ ′ x such that (i) for all z ⊑ ′ y, z ̸ ∈ X ′."
